<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,353,1063]" box="[151,1196,353,380]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">
The 18 species placed in this subgenus (clades B–E of 
<bibRefCitation author="Kahnt, B. &amp; Montgomery, G. A. &amp; Murray, E. &amp; Kuhlmann, M. &amp; Pauw, A. &amp; Michez, D. &amp; Paxton, R. J. &amp; Danforth, B. N." box="[766,962,353,380]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" pagination="95 - 105" refId="ref5545" refString="Kahnt, B., Montgomery, G. A., Murray, E., Kuhlmann, M., Pauw, A., Michez, D., Paxton, R. J. &amp; Danforth, B. N. (2017) Playing with extremes: Origins and evolution of exaggerated female forelegs in South African Rediviva bees. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 115, 95 - 105. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2017.07.025" type="journal article" year="2017">
Kahnt 
<emphasis box="[841,890,353,379]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
) are listed in table 1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="326" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,353,1063]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,389,416]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This is the most speciose subgenus comprising 18 species (Table 1); 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="2008" box="[1106,1270,389,415]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transkeiana">
<emphasis box="[1106,1270,389,415]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">R. transkeiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
likely belongs here, too.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,353,1063]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">
Males combine the following characters: S7 with usually large strigate translucent lateral lobes (lateral lobes either missing or smooth in other subgenera); median lobes long and narrow lanceolate to spatulate with pilosity mostly restricted to the apical third, longest hairs about half as long as length of median lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1215,1287,533,560]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1652,1677]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,181,1627]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♂: a. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate; b. metasomal ster- num 7, dorsal view. R. (s. str.) macgregori Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♂: c. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate; d. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view. R. (s. str.) longimanus Michener ♂: e. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view (ll: lateral lobe; ml: median lobe); f. metasomal sternum 7, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889571" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889571/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">Figs 4</figureCitation>
e–f) (in other subgenera median lobes much shorter, of different form and hairs shorter). In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vogel &amp; Michener" authorityYear="1985" box="[1033,1183,569,595]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emdeorum">
<emphasis box="[1033,1183,569,595]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">R. emdeorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="2001" box="[1239,1346,570,595]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurata">
<emphasis box="[1239,1346,570,595]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">R. aurata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
median lobes are shorter (
<bibRefCitation author="Whitehead, V. B. &amp; Steiner, K. E." box="[353,661,605,631]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" pagination="143 - 277" refId="ref6735" refString="Whitehead, V. B. &amp; Steiner, K. E. (2001) Oil-collecting bees of the winter rainfall area of South Africa (Melittidae, Rediviva). Annals of the South African Museum, 108, 143 - 277." type="journal article" year="2001">Whitehead &amp; Steiner 2001</bibRefCitation>
: Figs 25B–C) and both have a vestigial pygidial plate (
<bibRefCitation author="Whitehead, V. B. &amp; Steiner, K. E." pageId="8" pageNumber="326" pagination="143 - 277" refId="ref6735" refString="Whitehead, V. B. &amp; Steiner, K. E. (2001) Oil-collecting bees of the winter rainfall area of South Africa (Melittidae, Rediviva). Annals of the South African Museum, 108, 143 - 277." type="journal article" year="2001">Whitehead &amp; Steiner 2001</bibRefCitation>
: Fig. 44F) that is absent in all other species. Males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="2001" box="[909,1071,642,667]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macgregori">
<emphasis box="[909,1071,642,667]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">R. macgregori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are divergent in that the median lobes are relatively short and completely covered with hair (
<figureCitation box="[824,909,677,704]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1652,1677]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,181,1627]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♂: a. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate; b. metasomal ster- num 7, dorsal view. R. (s. str.) macgregori Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♂: c. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate; d. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view. R. (s. str.) longimanus Michener ♂: e. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view (ll: lateral lobe; ml: median lobe); f. metasomal sternum 7, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889571" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889571/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,353,1063]" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">
Females can be identified by a combination of the following character states: broadened hind tibia and basitarsus with the scopa consisting of densely plumose pubescence for transporting floral oil (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1237,749,776]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,182,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[192,1395,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: a. metasoma with distinct white apical hair bands. R. (s. str.) whiteheadi Kuhlmann ♀: b. metasoma with indistinct yellowish apical hair bands. R. (Redivivoides) capensis (Kuhlmann) ♀: c. hind leg. R. (Deriviva) intermedia Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: d. front leg, coxa with apical hairy spine (s). R. (Deriviva) intermixta Cockerell ♀: e. hind basitarsus with shiny scale-like projection; f. hind leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889569/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Michener" authorityYear="1981" box="[1293,1436,749,775]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Redivivoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1293,1436,749,775]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">Redivivoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
hind tibia not broadened and without plumose pubescence), bidentate mandible (tridentate in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez, 2020" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[1198,1301,786,812]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Gigaviva">
<emphasis box="[1198,1301,786,812]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">Gigaviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and inconspicuous yellowish apical tergal hair bands (
<figureCitation box="[648,730,821,848]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,182,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[192,1395,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: a. metasoma with distinct white apical hair bands. R. (s. str.) whiteheadi Kuhlmann ♀: b. metasoma with indistinct yellowish apical hair bands. R. (Redivivoides) capensis (Kuhlmann) ♀: c. hind leg. R. (Deriviva) intermedia Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: d. front leg, coxa with apical hairy spine (s). R. (Deriviva) intermixta Cockerell ♀: e. hind basitarsus with shiny scale-like projection; f. hind leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889569/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
) (distinctly white in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez, 2020" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[964,1057,821,847]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Albiviva">
<emphasis box="[964,1057,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">Albiviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in combination with the absence of a scale-like projection on the distal-dorsal angle of the hind basitarsus (present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez, 2020" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[1110,1203,857,883]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Albiviva">
<emphasis box="[1110,1203,857,883]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">Albiviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and three species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,249,894,919]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Deriviva">
<emphasis box="[151,249,894,919]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">Deriviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="2001" box="[264,417,893,919]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis box="[264,417,893,919]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">R. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[431,578,894,919]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermixta">
<emphasis box="[431,578,894,919]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">R. intermixta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[633,743,894,920]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Redivivoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipes">
<emphasis box="[633,743,894,920]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">R. rufipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). This set of characters also applies to females of two species in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[332,430,930,955]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Deriviva">
<emphasis box="[332,430,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">Deriviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, namely 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Michener" authorityYear="1981" box="[533,659,929,955]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colorata">
<emphasis box="[533,659,929,955]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="326">R. colorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
